          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Use a concise group label that frames the decision.</li>
                <li>Always pre-select a sensible default when one exists.</li>
                <li>Keep option labels to 1&#8211;4 words.</li>
                <li>Group semantically related options together.</li>
                <li>Show an error state + help text together.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Leave the group unlabelled.</li>
                <li>Leave all options unselected if a default makes sense.</li>
                <li>Write full sentences as radio labels.</li>
                <li>Mix unrelated options in a single group.</li>
                <li>Show only a red border without explaining what went wrong.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
