                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">When the user must choose <strong>exactly one</strong> option from a small, finite list (2&#8211;6 options).</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">When all options need to be visible at once without interaction.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">For settings or configuration screens where the full set of choices is informative.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>When NOT to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Multiple selections</strong> &#8212; use Checkbox Group.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Long lists (7+)</strong> &#8212; use Select Box to save vertical space.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Binary yes/no with immediate effect</strong> &#8212; use Toggle.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;"><strong>Yes/No inside a form</strong> &#8212; a single Checkbox may suffice.</li>
                </ul>
