          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="layout-guidance" class="doc-section-title">Layout Guidance</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Choose the right layout based on available space and label length.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Layout</th><th>Default?</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>Left</strong></td><td>Yes (web)</td><td>Options are laid out horizontally in a row. Default for all standard responsive web layouts.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Top</strong></td><td>Special case</td><td>Options stack vertically below the group label. Use only when horizontal space is severely constrained, for mobile viewports, or when options have long labels that wrap.</td></tr>
