          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective radio button usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Concise group label:</strong> Frame the decision clearly with a short group label.</li>
                <li><strong>Pre-select a default:</strong> Always pre-select a sensible default when one exists.</li>
                <li><strong>Use Left layout:</strong> Use the default Left layout for standard web forms.</li>
                <li><strong>Error + help text:</strong> Show an error state and help text together.</li>
                <li><strong>Short labels:</strong> Keep option labels to 1&#8211;4 words.</li>
                <li><strong>Semantic grouping:</strong> Group semantically related options together.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>No unlabelled groups:</strong> Don't leave the group unlabelled.</li>
                <li><strong>No empty selection:</strong> Don't leave all options unselected if a default makes sense.</li>
                <li><strong>Avoid Top layout:</strong> Switch to Top layout only when labels are very long or horizontal space is unavailable.</li>
                <li><strong>No red-only errors:</strong> Don't show only a red border without explaining what went wrong.</li>
                <li><strong>No full sentences:</strong> Don't write full sentences as radio labels.</li>
                <li><strong>No mixed groups:</strong> Don't mix unrelated options in a single group.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

